SpecRest/IR.lean drift queue
===========================

Intent
------

Anyone who modifies `modules/ir/src/main/scala/specrest/ir/Types.scala`'s
`Expr`, `BinOp`, `UnOp`, or declaration ADTs in a way that affects the
verified subset (see `10_translator_soundness.md` §14) records the diff
here and updates `STATUS.md` in the same PR. The PR template carries
the reminder.

This file is intentionally not Lean source (no `.lean` extension): it
should never be loaded by `lake build`, and its presence does not affect
proof state.

Queued expansions for M_L.2 (issue #128)
----------------------------------------

- `Prime` / `Pre` for two-state coupling.
  Will require Env + State_pre + State_post triple in `eval`.

- `With` for record-update semantics.

- `UnaryOp(Cardinality)` restricted to state-relation references.

- `FieldAccess` on entity-typed values.
  Needs explicit per-field accessor functions in the embedding.

- `Index` restricted to state-relation references.

- `Quantifier(Some)` over enums (mirror of `Quantifier(All)`).

State carrier: now in scope (delivered by M_L.1)
-------------------------------------------------

`State` is `{ scalars : List (String × Value), relations : List (String × List Value) }`.
M_L.2 will extend this to a pair `(State_pre, State_post)` to encode `Prime`/`Pre`
two-state semantics.

Drift log
---------

2026-05-02 — M_L.4.h: added `Expr.fieldAccess` (entity-typed state-scalar
  field read). Strictly-additive carrier extension: `State.entityFields :
  List (String × List (String × Value))` and `SmtModel.predFields : List
  (String × List (String × SmtVal))`. New `lookupField_correlated` mutual
  lemma + `lookup_map_entityFields` + `lookup_map_stringValue` helpers.
  Universal `soundness` extended with the new arm — still closes with zero
  `sorry`. Mirrors `Translator.scala:981-1005`. Restricted to bare-Identifier
  base (`scalar.field`).

2026-05-02 — M_L.4.g: added `Expr.indexRel` (state-relation pair lookup).
  Strictly-additive carrier extension: `State.lookups : List (String × List
  (Value × Value))` and `SmtModel.predLookup : List (String × List (SmtVal ×
  SmtVal))`. Existing `relations` and `predDomain` fields unchanged so
  `In/NotIn/Cardinality/forallRel` soundness is untouched. New
  `lookupKey_correlated` mutual-induction lemma + `find_map_valueToSmt` helper
  bridge the Lean/SMT lookup tables. Universal `soundness` extended with the
  new arm — still closes with zero `sorry`.

2026-05-02 — M_L.4.f: added `Expr.forallRel` (universal quantifier over
  state-relation domains). New `SmtTerm.forallRel` + `evalForallRel` mutual
  helper in `Semantics.lean` + `evalForallRel_correlated` mutual-induction
  lemma + `soundness_forallRel_known` per-case theorem in `Soundness.lean`.
  Universal `soundness` extended with the new arm — still closes with zero
  `sorry`. Emit-side disambiguation via `ir.enums.map(_.name).toSet`.

2026-05-01 — M_L.1 (#127): renamed `Expr.intCmp` → `Expr.cmp` and broadened
  `eq`/`neq` to polymorphic `Value` equality. Added `Expr.member`,
  `Expr.forallEnum`. Added `TypeExpr`, `EntityDecl`, `FieldDecl`. Reshaped
  `StateDecl` into `scalars : List StateScalar` + `relations : List StateRelation`
  (was `fields : List StateField` with a `isInt : Bool` flag). Added
  `OperationDecl.ensures`. Added `ServiceIR.entities`. Per-operator denotation
  lemmas now live in `SpecRest/Lemmas.lean`.
